==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sulpician
<hw>Sul*pi"cian</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So called after
the parish of St. <ets>Sulpice</ets> in Paris, of which the founder,
Jean Jacques Olier, was pastor in 1643.]</ety> <fld>(R. C. Ch.)</fld>
<def>One of an order of priests established in France in 1642 to educate
men for the ministry. The order was introduced soon afterwards into
Canada, and in 1791 into the United States.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>Sulpitian</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sultan</ent>⟦br⟧
